Surna Inc. Key Developments

Surna Inc. Announces Board Changes
May 31 17
On May 31, 2017, Morgan Paxhia notified the Board of Directors of Surna Inc. of his resignation from the Board effective May 31, 2017. Effective May 31, 2017, the Board appointed J. Taylor Simonton and Chris Bechtel to fill the positions vacated by the resignation of Stephen Keen on May 10, 2017 and Morgan Paxhia. Messrs. Simonton and Bechtel will serve as directors until the next annual meeting of shareholders and until their respective successor is duly elected and qualified. In connection with the appointments of Messrs. Simonton and Bechtel, the Board determined that Messrs. Simonton and Bechtel are "independent directors" as such term is defined in Rule 5605(a)(2) of the NASDAQ Stock Market. Mr. Simonton spent 35 years at PricewaterhouseCoopers, LLC including 23 years as a partner in the firm's Assurance Services, before retiring in 2001. Mr. Simonton was a partner for seven years in PwC's National Professional Services Group, which handles the firm's auditing and accounting standards, SEC, corporate governance, risk management and quality matters. He has extensive experience with SEC filings, including assistance with over 100 initial public offerings during his PwC career. Mr. Bechtel has over 30 years' experience, as an executive, entrepreneur and consultant, managing and advising businesses from start-ups to divisions of large Fortune 500 companies. Since 2015, Mr. Bechtel has been the principal of Bechtel Consulting, LLC. In September 2014, Mr. Bechtel joined the advisory board of Supreme Pharmaceuticals Inc.


Surna Inc. Reports Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the First Quarter Ended of March 31, 2017
May 15 17
Surna Inc. reported unaudited consolidated earnings results for the first quarter ended of March 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company’s revenue was approximately $1,593,000 compared to $2,498,000 for the three months ended March 31, 2016, a decline of $905,000, or 36%.  The decline in revenue was primarily due to the restructuring of the policies to secure sales contracts at an earlier stage which was not in place in first quarter of 2016. Operating loss was $589,618 compared to operating income of $364,979 a year ago. Loss from continuing operations before provision for income taxes was $1,000,829 compared to $746,214 a year ago. Basic and diluted loss per common share was $0.01 compared to $0.01 a year ago.


Surna Inc. Announces the Resignation of Stephen Keen as Director of the Board and Director of Technology, with Effect from April 28, 2017
Apr 18 17
Surna Inc. announced the board of directors is adjusting its membership to consist of three independent and two executive directors. The board has begun its search for an independent financial expert who will serve as the Audit Committee Chair. Effective April 28, 2017, Stephen Keen will resign as both Director of the Board and Director of Technology for the company. As announced in October 2016, the company has planned for Mr. Keen's departure coinciding with his increasing leadership of Sterling Pharms, his new cultivation entity that has agreed to provide efficiency and efficacy testing and act as a reference site for Surna's prospective customers.  Surna and Sterling Pharms are unaffiliated entities.


