			Company Description 


			Surna, Inc. engages in the development, design, and distribution of cultivation technologies for controlled environment agriculture primarily for cannabis crops. Its products include Surna Chillers, which refers to the liquid-based process cooling system for thermal cooling solution which covers ind...
		


                Surna, Inc. engages in the development, design, and distribution of cultivation technologies for controlled environment agriculture primarily for cannabis crops. Its products include Surna Chillers, which refers to the liquid-based process cooling system for thermal cooling solution which covers indoor crops such as cannabis; Surna Reflectors which refers to the reflector that optimizes light delivery to the plant canopy; and Bio-Security which offers a full-service air sanitation technology program for mold and mildew risk mitigation to cultivators. It also provides automation and hybrid building services. The company was founded on October 15, 2009 and is headquartered in Boulder, CO.
            




